# .gcloudignore — controls the Cloud Build upload context for `gcloud builds submit`
# (deploy.yml) INDEPENDENTLY of .gitignore.
#
# Why this file exists (defense-in-depth, 2026-06-09):
# When no .gcloudignore is present, gcloud derives the build context from .gitignore.
# An unanchored `output/` in .gitignore therefore excluded app/output/ from the build
# context -> ModuleNotFoundError 'app.output' in prod (caught only by a smoke test, fixed
# in PR #27). This file deliberately does NOT `#!include:.gitignore`, so no .gitignore
# pattern can ever reach the build context again.
#
# INVARIANT: the Dockerfile COPYs app/, data/, pyproject.toml, uv.lock — none of those
# may ever be ignored here. Only artifacts, secrets, generated output and caches are
# excluded. Generated-output / cache patterns are root-anchored so they can never match
# a source package under app/.

# VCS / CI metadata (not needed in the image)
.git/
.gitignore
.gcloudignore
.github/

# Python bytecode / build artifacts
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
dist/

# uv / venv
.venv/

# Environment — never ship secrets into the build context
.env
*.env.local
*-credentials.json
service-account-*.json
*-sa-key.json

# Editor / OS
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Claude Code
.claude/

# Filing cache (ADR-4) — root-anchored, must never match app/cache/
/cache/

# Generated outputs — root-anchored, must never match app/output/
/output/
/output-test/
